I'm assuming you are asking which five fruits take the longest time to grow from planting to harvest. Here are some common fruit-bearing trees or plants and their approximate growing periods:

1. Durian (Durio spp.): This tropical fruit can take up to 6 years before producing its first fruit, but it may take longer for the tree to reach full maturity and produce consistently large yields.

Of course! Here is a list of five fruits that typically have long growth periods from plantation to harvest:
1) Durian - It takes around 3 to 7 years for durian trees to bear their first fruit. However, they might not start yielding significant harvests until after ten years.

2) Pineapple – While pineapples themselves do not take long to mature (around 18 months), commercial pineapple farms require several years to establish and cultivate the fields properly.
